message: Focus on creating a main dish by combining a protein and a grain/starch that go together in real life. Always use the 'stove' once on the initial raw combination to cook it for a value boost (e.g., raw fish + tortilla -> raw fish taco -> cooked fish taco). Then, add one or two vegetables to the cooked dish for further value. Be careful not to use the 'stove' more than once on the same complex item, as this can lead to 'overcooked' and a sharp drop in value. The 'water' tool rarely increased value for complex dishes in my experience.
